      <head>Hermine Schiff (née Hahn)</head>
      <div>

        <p>Wife of <ref cRef="entity-006733">Louis Schiff</ref>, sister-in-law of <ref
            cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Schiff)</ref> thus
          after 1919 also of <ref cRef="entity-000632">Heinrich Schenker</ref>; mother of <ref
            cRef="entity-008447">Trude Schiff</ref> and Wilhelm Schiff.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Hermine was the second of the five children of Julius Hahn (c1849–) and Josefa (<hi
            rend="italic">née</hi> Tausig) (1852–). Nothing is known of her childhood or education.
          She married <ref cRef="entity-006733">Louis Schiff</ref> and the couple had two children:
            <ref cRef="entity-008447">Trude Schiff</ref> and Wilhelm Schiff.</p>

        <p>In April 1936, the family was still living in <ref cRef="entity-002248">Ústí nad
            Labem</ref>, where they were visited by <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette
            Schenker</ref> at the outset of her six-month journey to and from <ref
            cRef="entity-005845">Chile</ref>, and where she met <ref cRef="entity-006733"
            >Louis</ref>, Hermine, <ref cRef="entity-008447">Trude</ref>, and probably her two
          grandchildren, all of whom were “kind and considerate” to her. Nothing is known of the
          remainder of her life or that of <ref cRef="entity-006733">Louis</ref> (<ref
            cRef="entity-008447">Trude</ref> perished in <ref cRef="entity-007493">Auschwitz</ref>),
          as did several other members of the Schiff family.</p>
      </div>

